args: Your Highness! Captain Leif!\nI have returned!
Welcome back, Patia. Thanks for all of\nyour hard work.
Yes, that's quite a long trip.\nSo what did Cecile say?
She has agreed to help us. However...
The moment we arrived, she fell into\nsomething of a state.
Come now, Cecile. There is no reason for\nfear; the prince of this castle is a good and\nkind man of the highest regard.

Hi there, Cecile. You were part of my
father's royal guard, right? I remember
seeing you around the castle quite a bit
when I was younger.
You remember me, Your Highness?\nI...I am not worthy of such honors!
Heh. There's no need for that kind of\nformality around here. Besides, I'm not\nnearly so magnificent a ruler as my father.
Though I'm told that makes me a lot easier\nto get along with, so just try to relax and\nbe yourself as best you can.
In time, I hope you come to think of this\ncastle as your home!

That's right. This castle—and by extension
the nation—was founded on the notion of
bringing peace to the people. As prince,
I have to create and protect such places.
Then your goal is to create a castle and\nnation where everyone can be at peace...?
Not so different from the knight's code we\nonce swore. Wouldn't you agree, Cecile?
Well, it's different from the strength\nthat King Aurelius aimed for with the\nformer Alberia, but...
But honestly, I think the way you run this\nnation is pretty darn great!
So tell me, Cecile: Are you interested in\nserving your nation as a knight once more?

The White Sparrows are running short on
good recruits, and having you here would
do a great deal to put my mind at ease.
What do you say?
Huh?! Well, I'd be honored, but I...\nI mean, I don't...
Cecile, wait! Where are you going?!
She's probably heading for her new room.\nCome on!
I know you are in there Cecile. Please,\nyou must come out so we can talk about\nthis without a door to block our words.

Nuuuuh uh! No way, nope, nope, nope!
Even after His Highness went out of his
way to be nice to me, I STILL couldn't live
up to his expectations!
I don't have the courage to answer him...\nAnd I don't want to think about why...\nI DON'T WANT TO FACE WHAT I AM!
Cecile, I know you came here because you\nwish to do just that—to face the knightly\npath once more.
It sounds like Cecile is dead-set on staying\nin there for quite some time.
We need a plan to get her out—and I\nthink I may know just the thing...
(Okay, it's quiet. I think they all left.\nSo now...)
Aaaah, Manachew! I'm gonna munch\non you so good!
Huh?! Hey! Wh-who's there?\nWho's hitting my window?
It's me, Cecile! Please open up!
Patia? Hey, I know that ladder—it's the\none the White Sparrows use for castle\nsieges! Did Leif put you up to this?

(Back during the territorial disputes in
former Alberia, we turned the tides against
the impenetrable Balmore Keep with a
single window and this ladder.)
(We called it Operation Schlep Ladder,\nand I'm pretty sure Leif was the one who\ncame up with it.)
Leif was always careful to observe his\nenemy's strongholds, so this is just like\nhim. Well, I'm not gonna fall for it!
I'm gonna take that ladder down\nonce and for all!
Cecile?! Why are you pointing your\nmanacaster at the ladder?!
Sorry, Patia. But I'm not coming out!
Don't worry. I calculated the angle so you\nwould fall right into that pile of laundry\nin the courtyard.
(It seems Leif wants to get me out of here \nno matter what.)
(Well, he'll just have to deal, because if I\nleave, I have to respond to His Highness.)
(And that means admitting to his face that\nI'm not fit to be a knight.)
(So I'm just gonna stay in this room until\nI turn old and gray and wrinkly!)
(It came from the other side of the door.\nWait, could it be...?)
*pant* *wheeze* I'm back. Also, this\nCecile person is seriously stubborn.
Look, just let me break down the door\nalready. I promise to install another one.\nOkay? Great, thanks. Hiiii-ya!
GYAAAA! Ow! What the hell?\nI nearly burned my hand off!
I knew it. This is the same plan Cecile\ncame up with when the southern tribes\nwere laying siege to us at Fort Hann.

We used flame mana to heat the iron at
the main gate, from the the iron lattice to
the chains on the bridge. It got so hot,
the invading forces couldn't touch them.

It was a simple tactic, but effective
against the southern tribes who knew so
little of magic. Still I never thought to see
it used here in my own house...
Cecile can use that kind of high-level\nmagic?
Oh, no, I imagine she extracted the mana\nfrom one of the bullets of her caster and\nused that to deploy the trick.
She can disassemble a bullet and use the\nmana within? She really is an experienced\nsoldier... But...
Oh, uh...just wondering why we're fighting\nso hard to make her leave her room in the\nfirst place.
Your Highness! Is everything all right?
After hearing what Cecile's been going\nthrough, I spent some time thinking\nabout it.
And if she doesn't want to join with us,\nshe absolutely doesn't have to.
Allow me to thank you for your kind words\nin Cecile's stead, Highness. However...
Deep down, I know she wants to serve you.
If she truly did not wish to join with the\nSparrows, she would have fled the castle.\nYet instead she absconded to her room.
She is trapped, Your Highness—trapped\nbetween wanting to serve you and being\ndismayed that she is yet unable to.
I see. Well then, how about this?
Why don't you just hire Cecile on\nas a mercenary?
Er, I'm sorry. You want ME to hire her?
Yes. It's clearly too difficult for her to\ndedicate herself to me right now, but as\nyou said, she still wants to help.
And if you hire her as a mercenary,\nshe'll take orders from you. Not me.
If she ever decides she wants to try being\na knight again someday, we can talk about\nthat when the time is right.
Please think about it, Cecile. There are\nmany ways to serve your country besides\ntaking up the mantle of knighthood.
You came back here to fight for Alberia,\ndidn't you?
I can't believe you'd wait this long for a\nloser like me.
Persistence brings victory against any\nsiege. That is a strategy you taught me\nlong, long ago.
Hah hah, that brings back memories...\nHey, so, Leif? Would you really hire me?\nAs a mercenary, I mean. For now.
